## 7. **DEPLOYMENT INSTRUCTIONS - UPDATED**

### **âœ… Local Development Setup:**

```bash
# 1. Clone and navigate to project
cd "C:\Users\[USER]\SCC-WEBAPP"

# 2. Start Backend Server
cd server
npm install
npm run dev
# Backend runs on: http://localhost:9090

# 3. Start Frontend (new terminal)
cd ../client
npm install
npm run dev
# Frontend runs on: http://localhost:5173
```

### **âœ… Production Deployment Options:**

#### **Option 1: Toolforge (Pre-configured)**
```yaml
# .toolforge.yaml already configured
type: webservice
runtime: node20
healthcheck_path: /api/health
memory: 512Mi
cpu: 0.5
replicas: 1
```

#### **Option 2: Heroku + Netlify**
```bash
# Backend to Heroku
heroku create scc-backend
git push heroku main

# Frontend to Netlify
npm run build
netlify deploy --prod --dir=dist
```

#### **Option 3: Docker Deployment**
```dockerfile
# Dockerfile for full-stack deployment
FROM node:20-alpine
WORKDIR /app
COPY . .
RUN npm run build
EXPOSE 9090 5173
CMD ["npm", "start"]
```

### **âœ… Environment Configuration:**
```env
# Backend (.env)
PORT=9090
NODE_ENV=production
WIKIDATA_API=https://query.wikidata.org/sparql

# Frontend (.env)
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:9090
VITE_APP_TITLE=Supreme Court Cases
```

